# Retire shepherd and update the orchestration docs

## Question

The bridge covers pane death for ALL panes (not just pi), so shepherd's remaining value is ~zero. Uninstall the herdr-shepherd Claude plugin (or document why any sliver stays), and update `~/.claude/skills/herdr-orchestration/SKILL.md`: the monitoring section's fallback ladder drops shepherd, crash detection is now spool-native (`pane_exited`), and the plugin install/setup/doctor flow is the documented entry point. Only verified behavior gets documented. Also check whether the fleet's herdr-aware graft block should mention the plugin (keep it terse — probably just the skill).

Resolution: what was removed, the updated skill section, and the herdr-pings README cross-check.

## Resolution (2026-07-12)

- `claude plugin uninstall herdr-shepherd` — succeeded (scope: user). Nothing retained: the bridge covers pane death for ALL panes, better than shepherd's polling ever did.
- `~/.claude/skills/herdr-orchestration/SKILL.md` rewritten: herdr-pings plugin install/setup/doctor is the documented entry point; crash detection is spool-native for every pane; `agent wait` remains only as the turn-end fallback for claude/codex workers; nested-`pi -p` spool gotcha documented; naming discipline notes that pi worker panes now name themselves via herdr-name-sync.
- The fleet herdr-aware graft block left unchanged (terse pointer stands; the skill carries the detail).
